<SLUG> BC-FBC-UCLA-LADN </SLUG>
 
McNOWN'S CENTERFOLD 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Which is better for a Heisman Trophy campaign _
throwing touchdowns or throwing up? UCLA quarterback Cade McNown
will find out soon enough.
</P>
<P>
   Sports Illustrated photographed McNown vomiting in the Oregon
game and has published it (full-color) on the contents page of its
current issue.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's good for the country to see Cade's human side,'' UCLA
media-relations director Marc Dellins said. ``Not unlike when
Rodney Peete had the measles 10 years ago, we'll figure out a way
to make it work to Cade's advantage.''
</P>
<P>
   The issue circulated through UCLA's Morgan Center and the locker
room. Most of the Bruins laughed, then said, ``I've got to get a
copy.''
</P>
<P>
   Bruins coach Bob Toledo was one of the first to see it.
</P>
<P>
   ``I grabbed it, took it to the quarterbacks meeting, then I took
it to every meeting room,'' Toledo said. ``It's funny, but it's not
funny.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Westwood reaction: USC coach Paul Hackett's comment that
Oregon is the Pac-10's best team whipped through Westwood faster
than Sports Illustrated.
</P>
<P>
   ``I mentioned it to the team,'' Toledo said. ``It's a comment
that was made. I tell the players not to make bulletin-board
material.
</P>
<P>
   ``Anytime coaches make comments or players make comments, I save
them.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Something must give: Cal has allowed 33 sacks this season,
most in the Pac-10. UCLA's defensive line has no sacks.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a big concern,'' Toledo said. ``There's no reason we
can't have a defensive lineman with one sack after five games.
</P>
<P>
   ``They're getting tied up. They're not using the techniques
they're being taught. They're freezing their feet and getting
locked up on people.''
</P>
<P>
   __ BCS update: If the season ended today, UCLA would play Ohio
State for the national championship in the Fiesta Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   USA Today computed the top teams based on the Bowl Championship
Series formula, which averages top-25 rankings and computer
rankings, then adds a strength-of-schedule quotient and one point
per defeat.
</P>
<P>
   The teams with the fewest points in the final BCS poll (Dec. 6)
will play in the Fiesta Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Ohio State is No. 1, with 3.45 points. UCLA is No. 2, with 3.71
points, followed by Tennessee (7.15) and Kansas State (7.55).
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-22-98 0253EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
