<HEADER>
A0649 &Cx1f; tic-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-CARDS-NOTEBOOK-AZ     10-22 0402
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDS-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INJURED MCCLESKEY ACHING TO PLAY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, ARIZ. - Here's how badly Cardinals cornerback  &UR; J.J.
McCleskey wants to play against Detroit on Nov. 1:
</P>
<P>
   ``You'll see me there in a wheelchair, if I have to,'' said
McCleskey, who has missed four consecutive games because of a knee
injury.
</P>
<P>
   McCleskey returned to practice Wednesday for the first time
since undergoing arthroscopic surgery on his right knee on Sept.
24.
</P>
<P>
   ``It has been very frustrating,'' said McCleskey, who was
starting right cornerback for much of training camp while  &UR; Tom
Knight was sidelined because of a shoulder injury. ``Seeing people
make plays and not make plays, I figured I could do it. I'm a
confident player.''
</P>
<P>
   Coach  &UR; Vince Tobin said McCleskey has been missed.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's a very, very tough and physical player who isn't very
big,'' said Tobin of McCleskey, 5 feet 8, 184 pounds. ``He battles
you. He's a competitor and played well at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
   ``His knee was bothering him all of camp. Finally, he couldn't
go anymore. I'm anxious to see how well he can run, cut and cover
the next two weeks.'' &QL; 
Personal business &QL;
</P>
<P>
   While McCleskey returned, three other players missed practice.
</P>
<P>
   Starting defensive end  &UR; Simeon Rice, also bothered by a thigh
injury, returned to his hometown of Chicago to attend the funeral
of a friend.
</P>
<P>
   Starting defensive tackle  &UR; Mark Smith was in Alabama for the
birth of his first child.
</P>
<P>
   Backup free safety  &UR; Kwamie Lassiter was out of town to attend
the funeral of his aunt. &QL; 
Still hurting &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Offensive guard  &UR; Chris Dishman, who has missed three consecutive
games because of a neck injury, still hasn't returned to practice.
He reinjured his neck in last Thursday's practice.
</P>
<P>
   ``It concerns me because I don't know when he'll be back,''
Tobin said.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Jerome Daniels continues to start at left guard in Dishman's
absence. &QL; 
Short shots &QL; 
Fullback  &UR; Larry Centers is tied with Indianapolis'  &UR; Marshall Faulk
for the NFL lead among running backs in receptions with 33.
Centers' next catch will be the 500th of his career.
</P>
<P>
   The Cardinals, who have a bye this week, will practice today and
then take off Friday, Saturday and Sunday. They will resume
preparations for the Lions' game next Monday. They are 4-5 in games
after bye weeks. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-22-98 0302EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
