Illustrated. 378 pp. Chicago: The University of Chicago Press. $30.
In pursuit of sins of the flesh, American tourists flocked to
France.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-EMOTIONAL-NYTSF, WORKING WITH EMOTIONAL INTELLIGENCE, By
Daniel Goleman, 383 pp. New York: Bantam Books. $25.95. As
everybody knows. But there's more to it than that.
</P>
<P>
   ADDIE, By Mary Lee Settle, 237 pp. Columbia: University of South
Carolina Press. $24.95. Mary Lee Settle weaves her autobiography
around the life of her indomitable grandmother.
</P>
<P>
   MAX LERNER, Pilgrim in the Promised Land, By Sanford Lakoff, 323
pp. Chicago: The University of Chicago Press. $25. A biography of
Max Lerner offers a new examination of his views on Marx and sex.
