u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MOVIES-ORGAZMO-COX     10-22 0321
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIES-ORGAZMO-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `Orgazmo' an impotent comedy fare
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here's the joke: A pious Mormon boy needs to raise money so he
can marry his sweetheart in the Tabernacle back in Salt Lake City.
How does he get the cash? He becomes a porn star.
</P>
<P>
   That's the one-yuck plot behind ``Orgazmo,'' Trey Parker's
second feature. (He also directed the movie, ``Cannibal! The
Musical,'' adapted by Dad's Garage for its current stage run.) If
you like the dumb scatology of Parker's ``South Park,'' you'll
probably enjoy the movie's frat-house silliness. But just so you
know, 10 minutes of the Comedy Central cartoon tends to have more
cutting pop-culture satire than all of ``Orgazmo,'' which probably
could have told its story in a third of its actual running time.
</P>
<P>
   Parker plays Joe Young, a gosh-darn nice fellow devoted to his
toothpaste-commercial-ready girlfriend Lisa (Robyn Lynne Raab).
Stumbling into the porn ring run by Maxxx Orbison (Michael Dean
Jacobs), Joe is lured by the ready cash, and is soon donning the
superhero costume of the porn star Orgazmo. His sidekick,
Choda-Boy, is played by MIT graduate Ben (Dian Bachar), who fends
off screen criminals ... with sex toys. In his spare time, Ben has
developed a real life ``orgazmorator,'' a firearm that causes
instant, um, satisfaction in anyone who gets zapped by it.
</P>
<P>
   That's the level of the humor. The movie is surprisingly sweet
and goofy, but runs through its thin gimmick fast. By the way, the
NC-17 rating isn't for the simulated (comic) sex, but for frank
language.
</P>
<P>
   ``Orgazmo''
</P>
<P>
   Grade: C-
</P>
<P>
   Starring Trey Parker and Dian Bachar. Written and directed by
Parker. Rated NC-17. Phipps Plaza Theater. 1 hour, 35 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   The verdict: Think of it as ``Candide in the Land of the Money
Shot.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
