   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   LETTERS-BOOK _ It all started with a can of Coke. When Naomi
Shavin of Sandy Springs saw Santa Claus on a can during the
Christmas season, she told her dad how left out she felt that the
soda pop giant didn't have any Jewish symbols. On his advice, she
wrote to the company. Letter writing to the ``big big world''
quickly became a habit. Naomi recently published her letters in a
book, which she signs at Borders Books in Dunwoody on Thursday. Her
book also has scored her interviews on the Roseanne Show and Good
Morning America. (Hill, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 16. WITH
PHOTOS. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   HOSTESSGIFTS _ Gifts to squirrel away now that can be used as
stocking stuffers, for unexpected givers, and as hostess gifts.
$0-$25. (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   SINATRA-BOOK _ You've got to hand it to Pete Hamill. Here it is,
barely five months since Frank Sinatra died, and already the
colorful New York newspaperman and best-selling author (``A
Drinking Life,'' ``Snow in August'') has churned out a book that
purports to tell us ``Why Sinatra Matters.'' (Vejnoska, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TVSURFER-COLUMN _ Fox debuts ``Brimstone,'' about a guy sent out
from Hell to capture escapees out wreaking havoc on Earth (Harris);
plus UPN's ``Love Boat'' features a guest spot by wrestling
champ-of-champs Bill Goldberg. (Longino, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   PLEASANTVILLE-DANIELS _ TORONTO, Ontario _ Jeff Daniels looks
right at home behind the ice cream counter in ``Pleasantville.''
And who better to personify artistic passion in smalltown America
than Daniels? He calls ``Pleasantville'' the best movie he's ever
made. When your credits include the Oscar-winning ``Terms of
Endearment,'' Woody Allen's ``The Purple Rose of Cairo'' and
Jonathan Demme's ``Something Wild,'' that's quite a statement.
(Larens, Dayton Daily News). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE-MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   FIRST-MAMMOGRAM_Mammogram Q &AMP; A with Dr. Kristine Thayer, a Palm
Beach County surgeon who specializes in breast diseases, and
Melanie Nielsen, a radiologic technologist and manager of the
Comprehensive Breast Center at Good Samaritan Medical Center in
West Palm Beach. 48. (Franquet, Palm Beach Post) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   MAMMOGRAM-SIDE_Renee Riedl found a lump in her left breast on
St. Patrick's Day, 1990, and a lump in her right breast on Dec. 17,
1996. Breast cancer, both times.Two matching mastectomy scars _
horizontal lines about four inches long _ have replaced them. 22.
(Anna, Palm Beach Post) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   CANCER-LESBIANS _ Lesbian women are at higher risk for breast
cancer than most heterosexual women, but until recently they had no
place to turn for information and support. Before her death this
year, Dennie Doucher set out to change that. The result is a
network that has given lesbians not only support groups where they
can talk openly about how their cancer has affected their
sexuality, but also information and an informal doctors' referal
service. (Kim, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED
</P>
