   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-SPACE (Moscow) _ A cosmonaut and contemporary of John
Glenn reflects on the sorry state of the Russian space program. By
David Filipov. 1400 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; CONGRESS-FEINGOLD (Madison, Wis.) _ Democratic Sen. Russ
Feingold, who pushed an unsuccessful attempt to overhaul campaign
finance laws, rejects the ``soft money'' the overhaul would have
banned, much to the pleasure of his Republican opponent. By
Mitchell Zuckoff. 1450 words.
</P>
