<HEADER>
A1551 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FILM-ORGAZMO-TEX     10-22 0590
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FILM-ORGAZMO-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OH, THE ECSTASY OF IT ALL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TODD CAMP 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   In spite of its much-ballyhooed NC-17 rating, ``South Park''
co-creator Trey Parker's ``Orgazmo'' succeeds on two levels: as a
clever spoof of pornography, action films and the '60s ``Batman''
TV series; and as a surprisingly hilarious piece of ``adult''
humor.
</P>
<P>
   I stress ``adult'' because in a hypersensitive world where
parents schlep their 3-year-olds to R-rated fare such as ``Saving
Private Ryan'' and then whine about the violence, it's nice to see
a movie made explicitly for adults. Don't even ``think'' of
bringing the youngsters to this one unless you want to spend the
next three weeks engaged in uncomfortable Q &AMP; A sessions.
</P>
<P>
   Parker, in addition to his writing and directing duties, stars
as Mormon missionary Joe Young (no relation to the mighty big
monkey). Faced with the insurmountable task of converting jaded Los
Angelenos, Joe merrily troops door to door, undeterred by the rude
responses he incurs.
</P>
<P>
   When he's almost beaten to a pulp for disturbing an adult-film
shoot, Joe defends himself with such style that the director begs
him to star in his next picture _ as porno superhero Orgazmo.
</P>
<P>
   Joe refuses at first, until he realizes his substantial paycheck
will help bankroll his fiancee's dream wedding at the Mormon temple
in Salt Lake City. He decides to grin and bear it, and with the
help of his enthusiastic sidekick Choda Boy (Dian Bacher), he makes
the film a huge success _ which means ... you guessed it, sequel
time.
</P>
<P>
   But all bets are off when Joe's girlfriend finds out what he's
been up to and forbids him to make a follow-up. His enraged boss
has her kidnapped to persuade Joe to complete the picture, so it's
up to the ``real'' Orgazmo and Choda Boy to save the day.
</P>
<P>
   Many of the best bits in this picture are far too rude to
discuss in a family newspaper; suffice it to say, if it's been done
in a porn movie, it's discussed in graphic detail here. But unlike
the queasy voyeuristic feeling you got while watching ``Boogie
Nights'' with an audience, ``Orgazmo'' is so silly and over-the-top
that you can't possibly be offended by anything it has to say. And
its matter-of-fact, on-the-set banter is a much more accurate
depiction of adult film shoots then anything in ``Nights.''
</P>
<P>
   That's not to say that the film won't offend audiences _ as with
the foul-mouthed cartoon antics of ``South Park,'' ``Orgazmo'' has
more than its fair share of toilet humor. Flatulence jokes abound,
along with irreverent non-PC jabs at religion, gays, Asians and
African-Americans. But like ``South Park,'' it's an
equal-opportunity offender.
</P>
<P>
   Parker's ``South Park'' partner in crime, Matt Stone, co-stars
along with a host of real-life porn stars for audience members to
pretend not to recognize. As for the inevitable comparisons to
``There's Something About Mary,'' ``Orgazmo'' manages to be about
10 times as clever while outdoing ``Mary'' on the gross-humor meter
by far. Best of all, there's not a hair-gel joke in sight. Now
that's funny.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Film: ``Orgazmo''
</P>
<P>
   Rating: 3 1/2 on a scale of 5
</P>
<P>
   Director: Trey Parker
</P>
<P>
   Stars: Trey Parker, Dian Bacher
</P>
<P>
   Length: 95 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Rated: NC-17 _ rude humor, sexually explicit activity and
language, profanity and cartoon violence
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Todd Camp is a film critic for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
