   YANKS-HISTORY _ Even George Steinbrenner, the Yankees owner who
likes to brag on his baseball team, wasn't ready to say outright
that his team is the best ever, after they completed their stunning
125-victory season with a World Series sweep of San Diego on
Wednesday. There is no easy way to assign the 1998 Yankees their
rightful place in history, because while baseball's rules
essentially have remained the same, the sport has evolved in the
20th century. By Buster Olney. (With a photo.)
