<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    CHURCH ARSONS DECLINE AS PROSECUTIONS RISE
 &HT;    BY NICHOLE MONROE
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Church arsons have sharply declined in the face of
increased prosecutions, community intervention and media coverage,
a federal task force said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   About 114 church arsons, bombings or attempted bombings have
been investigated this year through September, compared with 297
incidents in 1996, according a report the National Church Arson
Task Force submitted to President Clinton.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton created the task force in 1996 after a rash of church
fires, concentrated in the South. Since then, the group has
investigated 670 cases, resulting in the arrest of 308 suspects.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
