<DOCNO> NYT19981022.0247 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-22 16:06 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1756 &Cx1f; tic-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ORGAZMO-MOVIE-AZR &LR;      10-22 0403
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ORGAZMO-MOVIE-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IMPOTENT `ORGAZMO' SINKS TO NEW LOW 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB FENSTER  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNDATED - When a movie is rated NC-17, it usually means that
anyone younger than 17 can't get into the theater. In the case of
``Orgazmo,''it should mean that anyone with an IQ over 17 doesn't
qualify.
</P>
<P>
   A sex farce released to capitalize on the success of Trey
Parker, one of the creators of TV's ``South Park,'' ``Orgazmo''
attempts to establish a new bottom for the barrel of pop culture.
</P>
<P>
   Parker is the writer, director and star of a movie aimed
strictly at the people who found ``Beavis and Butt-head'' too
intellectually challenging.
</P>
<P>
   He stars as Joe Young, a Mormon on a mission, who agrees to star
in a porno film so he can make enough money to marry his
girlfriend.
</P>
<P>
   The film details Joe's days on the set, where he gets morally
upset by the sex but has a stand-in, or lie-in, for the close-ups.
He also joins forces with another porno star (Dian Bachar) to have
silly fights with various thugs and battle the evil producer
(Michael Dean Jacobs).
</P>
<P>
   The comedy is abysmal, the acting too dumb to call camp, and
even the sex is stupid and boring.
</P>
<P>
   In other words, ``Orgazmo'' has the makings of a cult hit. Will
it end up as ``The Rocky Horror Picture Show ''of the next
millennium? If there is no level to which stupidity cannot sink, it
will.
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps Parker made ``Orgazmo'' to find out exactly how much he
can insult the intelligence of his fans and still take their money.
</P>
<P>
   The film is also grossly offending to Mormons, although that
implies some Mormons would actually see the movie to be offended,
and that seems unlikely.
</P>
<P>
   The only thing interesting about ``Orgazmo'' is how it got that
prohibitive NC-17 rating. Sure, it contains a little sex, some ugly
nudity and a heap of profanity. But so did ``Boogie Nights,'' which
was also about the porno-film industry but which was rated R.
</P>
<P>
   ``Orgazmo'' probably has less sex and nudity than ``Boogie
Nights,'' although it's far more offensive to anyone with even a
dreg of taste.
</P>
<P>
   It appears that the movie ratings board tried to stigmatize
``Orgazmo'' with the NC-17 simply because it's such a lousy movie,
while ``Boogie Nights'' is a serious, legitimate film. In other
words, the board is now judging filmmaking quality, not content
issues alone. 1 star. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-22-98 1606EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
