   DELTA-EARNINGS _ Delta Air Lines shareholders hold annual
meeting in New York. Delta's stock is up $1.37. (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   AIRTRAN-LAYOFFS _ Folo on Airtran's plans for employee cutbacks
in Orlando. Checking to see whether any are on the horizon in
Atlanta. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   NATURAL-GAS _ Major players in Georgia's newly deregulated
natural gas market give status report at Chamber of Commerce forum.
Atlanta Gas Light Co. reports difficulties in signing over
customers to new marketing companies. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   MEDAPHIS _ Medaphis takes a $390 million charge to write down
value of some of its businesses; takes over charges, including
previously announced one for settlement of government
investigation. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   SCI-ATLANTA _ Scientific-Atlanta announced the first commitment
by InterMedia to purchase Scientific- Atlanta's advanced digital
set-top devices and the network that supports them.
Scientific-Atlanta's Explorer(R) 2000 set-top box is the only
advanced interactive digital set-top box available for deployment.
(Haddad, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   INTELLIQUEST-EARN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ IntelliQuest Information
Group Inc. said Wednesday that a year of restructuring allowed it
to return to profitability in the third quarter. (Hawkins, Austin
American-Statesman). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   AMERICAN-AIRLINES _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Southwest Airlines, with its
cheap fares, no-frills flights and Dijon-and-orange 737s, has long
been the market leader in Austin skies. But last month, for the
first time in recent history, American Airlines edged out Southwest
in the number of passenger departures from Robert Mueller Municipal
Airport. It is a feat American accomplished, in large part, by
adding new service to Dallas Love Field and Houston Hobby. (Breyer,
Austin American-Statesman). MOVED
</P>
