to avoid troubles ahead.
</P>
<P>
   But this is a bad test. Central banks cannot and should not try
to prevent an overdue correction in share prices. They should only
cushion the economy from the worst consequences.
</P>
<P>
   The zeal with which Wall Street has cheered Greenspan's latest
rate cut shows that investors still miss the point: even in fairy
tales, what goes up does eventually come down.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
