   Reefers:
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-CHURCH (Washington) _ President Clinton has sent a
letter to members of his home church in Little Rock, Ark.,
expressing repentance for his actions and asking their forgiveness.
The church did not release the contents of the letter, and a church
spokesperson said the letter is intended to be a private, spiritual
message to the congregation. By Laurie Goodstein.
</P>
<P>
   FLOJO-AUTOPSY _ The autopsy report for Florence Griffith-Joyner
is released at a news conference. By Jere Longman.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-ANIMALS-THINKING (Undated) _ Animals do not have language
and therefore, savants from Descartes onward have held, cannot
think, because words are coin of thought. A strong hint that
animals can think, but in ways that do not involve language has
emerged from a study of Rosencrantz and MacDuff, two rhesus monkeys
whose cognitive skills are being explored at Columbia University in
New York. By Nicholas Wade.
</P>
