<HEADLINE>
HEAVENLY HERB ON MISSION STREET
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   A three-man team from Burning Alive Designs signed, sealed and
pronounced complete their 20-by-70-foot homage to the late
columnist  &UR; Herb Caen &LR;  on Columbus Day. Their new mural, on the side
of Big O Tires on Mission between Sixth and Seventh s &LR; treets,
pictures Caen's face beaming down at a San Francisco skyline as
angels flutter nearby. The line ``San Francisco is heaven on
earth'' is a sentiment that was often expressed by Caen.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Alex Eremian &LR; , &UR; Sandro Tchikovani  &LR; and  &UR; Richard Richey &LR; , who
worked on the mural for six weeks, were born and raised in San
Francisco. ``I read Caen's column a lot,'' said Eremian. ``He's a
San Francisco icon. ... We wanted to do something that is a
celebration of our home town.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
