   &UR; AUTOS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ABOUT-CARS-GRAND-AM (Undated) _ With 1999 models of the Grand Am
and the new Olds Alero _ Buick will no longer impose small cars on
the public _ General Motors has again promised a line of new and
improved models in this hard-to-define segment of the market (think
of them as jumbo compacts or junior midsize sedans). The Grand Am
fits neatly between the compact Sunfire _ a twin of the Chevy
Cavalier _ and the Grand Prix, which is at the large end of the
midsize segment. By James G. Cobb.
</P>
