</P>
<P>
   In a case that is sure to capture national attention, angry
investors are suing San Francisco fund manager Robert Pryt and his
broker-dealer, Bear Stearns, for mismanaging their money and
misrepresenting the fund's peformance, which was used to determine
how much Pryt got paid. Pryt folded his fund, BKP Partners, in June
after losing as much as $100 million, according to investors. By
columnist Mark Veverka
</P>
