<HEADLINE>
CLINTON ASKS HIS HOME CHURCH FOR FORGIVENESS 
</HEADLINE>
  (Duplication warning: Also moved in `w' category) 
(mk) 
 By LAURIE GOODSTEIN   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   President Clinton has sent a letter to the members of his home
church in Little Rock, Ark., expressing his repentance and asking
their forgiveness for his sins.
</P>
<P>
   The two-page, handwritten letter was read aloud to the
congregation of the church, Immanuel Baptist, at the close of
morning services on Sunday by the pastor, the Rev. Rex Horne. A
