   LA-BUSES (Los Angeles) _ The MTA board gave final approval for a
plan to increase the number of buses scheduled to be bought through
fiscal year 2004 from 1,313 to 2,095. That number still isn't
enough to satisify the Bus Riders Union, which won a court order
requiring the MTA to reduce overcrowding on buses; but the group
Thursday claimed much of the credit for pushing the MTA to acquire
more buses. By Doug Haberman. (Will move in the ``n'' California
news file.)
</P>
<P>
   DRUGS-IN-COURT (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles Superior Court judges
plan to ``just say no'' to marijuana, cocaine and other drugs in
their courtrooms. The Los Angeles Police Department and other law
enforcement agencies have received notice that starting Jan. 1,
narcotics evidence must be presented at trial in the form of
photographs. And the reason? Drugs in the form of evidence could be
unhealthy for folks in court. By Peter Hartlaub. (Will move in the
``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
