A2379 &Cx1f; taf-z
u f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-INTERNET-MUSIC-NYT &LR;      10-22 0472
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-INTERNET-MUSIC-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INTERNET MUSIC SELLERS TO MERGE 
</HEADLINE>
   (ATTN: N.Y., Pa.)  
(dl) 
 By SAUL HANSELL   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   After weeks of negotiation, CD Now and N2K, the two biggest
Internet music sellers, agreed to merge Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   The all-stock deal gives holders of CD Now 60 percent of the new
company and N2K holders 40 percent. That means that CD Now is
buying N2K for $7.83, a 42 percent premium over the $5.50 price its
stock closed at Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The stocks of both companies have plummeted in recent months to
well below their initial offering prices, and a small fraction of
the highs they reached in a brief exuberant love affair with
investors.
</P>
<P>
   The companies now hope that their merger will cut costs and win
back the hearts of investors who worried that neither of them had
the clout to fight off new competitors such as Amazon.com.
</P>
<P>
   ``We will have operating leverage from one brand, one service,
one back end and one management team. And we won't have to compete
against each other for marketing deals,'' said Jon Diamond, a
co-founder and vice chairman of N2K.
</P>
<P>
   Diamond will become the chairman of the new company. Jason Olim,
the president and chief executive of CD Now, will retain those
positions in the new company. Larry Rosen, N2K's chairman, and
David Grusin, another vice chairman, will serve on the company's
board but will not have management responsibility. Rosen is
recovering from heart surgery.
</P>
<P>
   The new company will use N2K's offices at 55 Broad St. in Lower
Manhattan as its headquarters. But it will retain operations in
suburban Philadelphia. CD Now is headquartered in Jenkinstown, Pa.,
and N2K has a facility nearby.
</P>
<P>
   Olim said there would be some layoffs but he declined to say how
many.
</P>
<P>
   Initially, the company will be called CD Now/N2K Inc., but the
company will hire consultants to help pick the brand and corporate
name. N2K's main store operates under the name Music Boulevard.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a smart strategic move,'' said Maria LaTour Kadison, a
senior analyst with Forrester Research. ``There is no reason for
the two of them to duke it out and grab market share from each
other.''
</P>
<P>
   But she said that Amazon still appears to have the upper hand,
even though it has just entered the music market.
</P>
<P>
   ``They simply have the brand recognition and loyal customer base
that these two combined don't have.''
</P>
<P>
   The companies said that they would have more than 1 million
customers and would be the third most visited store on the
Internet.
</P>
<P>
   N2K has focused more on providing articles, reviews and other
content related to music. It operates sites about the major music
genres including Rocktropolis, Jazz Central Station and Classical
Insites.
</P>
<P>
   CD Now has countered by licensing music content from MTV and
Rolling Stone.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
