<SLUG> BC-1ap1023a </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Marietta second-graders fly high with experiment
 &HT;    By Charles Seabrook and Diane R. Stepp
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Does your chewing gum lose its flavor on the shuttle overnight?
Does your popcorn pop or crayons melt when they fly into outer
space?
</P>
<P>
   These are things inquisitive second-grade students at Dowell
Elementary School in Marietta want to know, and NASA is going to
help them get the answers.
</P>
