Long-Term Capital Management, concedes he was blind to the huge
risks the fund was taking. ``I think the lesson of this is that if
it's structured so that you can't get more than a fraction of the
picture, then in the future we will be taking our business
elsewhere,'' he says. (Ozier Muhammad/New York Times Photo)
</P>
