The Greenland Family Farm in Cutchogue has a corn maze that is
expected to last through Halloween. It's nothing fancy, just a set
of paths cut through an acre of unusually tall corn (a red strain
called Butcher Block) with tacky Halloween-theme props to mark your
way. But the maze has become a ritual marker of fall. (Lois
Raimondo/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
