<SLUG> BC-AIRTOUCH-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 AirTouch Posts Record 3rd Quarter  &HT;       
 By Deborah Solomon 
 &HT;     c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
Strong demand for wireless service overseas boosted AirTouch
Communications Inc. to record third-quarter profit levels as the
No. 1 wireless carrier added more than 1 million new subscribers
this quarter.
<P>
   San Francisco's AirTouch reported a 59 percent increase in net
income from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
   The company earned $213 million (30 cents a share) compared to
$134 million (18 cents) a share in the third quarter of 1997.
</P>
<P>
   Revenues rose 24 percent to $1.96 billion from $1.58 billion
last year.
</P>
<P>
   Sam Ginn, AirTouch chief executive, said the company was not
harmed by the economic flux overseas that has hurt many companies
with international ventures.
</P>
<P>
   He said AirTouch's international operations added 735,000 new
customers.
</P>
<P>
   ``International is just exploding, and we expect to see huge
growth in the international market,'' Ginn said in an interview.
</P>
<P>
   The company, which beat Wall Street's estimates by at least 4
cents, plans to continue expanding into new markets, Ginn said.
</P>
<P>
   AirTouch stock closed up 25 cents at $53.50.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
